tps://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;citationneeded.news/i-am-my-ow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;n-legal-department/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://hachyderm.io/tags/newsletter" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;newsletter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://hachyderm.io/tags/CitationNeeded" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;CitationNeeded&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://hachyderm.io/tags/journalism" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;journalism&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://hachyderm.io/tags/IndependentMedia" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;IndependentMedia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113376050256041651</guid><pubDate>Sat, 26 Oct 2024 22:20:35 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Dan Gillmor</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@dangillmor/113376317327327362</link><description>It was hard to imagine circumstances -- given the NY Times' relentlessly terrible political coverage -- that would make the Times look good this year.But then came the craven capitulations to Trump by the owners of the LA Times and Washington Post -- vetoing even milquetoast endorsements of Harris. They made the Times, which didn't duck at least that duty, seem downright brave by comparison.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113376378406789808</guid><pubDate>Sat, 26 Oct 2024 23:44:02 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/113378973490067302</link><description>MDPI have lost their way. Or more likely never found it in the first place. h/t &lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mastodon.social/@deevybee"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;deevybee&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; I think we must conclude that paying for publication creates perverse incentives that are irresistible.But some form of the problem will remain for as long as people count publications rather than examine content. A fake paper costs 1/100th (?) of the research to produce a real one. Current incentives against low-quality production do not balance that massive factor.&lt;a href="https://pubpeer.com/publications/77E4AB0FFADF8913053B6CE8D61085#9" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;pubpeer.com/publications/77E4A&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;B0FFADF8913053B6CE8D61085#9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113378973490067302</guid><pubDate>Sun, 27 Oct 2024 10:44:00 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/113378977336855846</link><description>&lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mastodon.social/@deevybee"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;deevybee&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; Until publishing crap becomes a strong career negative, we are lost.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113378977336855846</guid><pubDate>Sun, 27 Oct 2024 10:44:59 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Noah Cook</title><link>https://med-mastodon.com/@UncivilServant/113374345935529963</link><description>&lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mstdn.social/@mcnado" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;mcnado&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; They also made the decision *after* they had already made endorsements for House and Senate races in both Maryland and Virginia.The Post has not rescinded those endorsements or explained the difference.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113378981549922140</guid><pubDate>Sun, 27 Oct 2024 10:46:03 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Manish Vij</title><link>https://sfba.social/@vij/113376784340211171</link><description>DEI for white people&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/113/376/784/479/050/439/original/bbe945090ea8ae06.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/113/376/784/479/050/439/original/bbe945090ea8ae06.jpg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113378990622870681</guid><pubDate>Sun, 27 Oct 2024 10:48:22 +0000</pubDate></item></channel></rss>